The Conservatives were at 47%, up 1% from Opinium's previous poll a week ago, against Labour's 32%, up 2%. LONDON British Prime Minister Theresa May's Conservative Party has a 15 point lead over the main opposition Labour Party ahead of a 8 June national election, according to an opinion poll conducted by Opinium Research.The Conservatives were at 47%, up 1% from Opinium's previous poll a week ago, against Labour's 32%, up 2%.The poll put the centrist Liberal Democrats on 8%, down 1%, and the anti-European Union UK Independence Party at 5%, down 2%.Opinium Research carried out an online survey of 2,003 UK adults from 9 to 12 May.